The paper focuses on user interface tools for graphical probabilistic models, which are commonly used in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses enhancements to probability wheel and bar graph, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses navigation through conditional probability tables, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and decision-making systems (cs.SI).
